reviews.pros: taught me many facets of retail management. did enjoy my time there.
reviews.cons: lack of training for course, was meant to be paid learning but do at own time. very difficult when doing such obscene hours. would hope it has since changed. Accrued leave at higher rate of pay was transferred to lower rate of pay with no warning. long hours
a lot of work to do

reviews.pros: Clear communication from senior management Aldi are always looking to promote the right people within their organisation Great management system for developing and retaining staff Great wages Depending on the store, because they run a small team you will see your team mates as your second family CEO and senior managers are hands on so you will see them come in every now and then to see how the stores are coping They have great discounts on gym and health insurance as well having a fund for when employees fall on hard times They are creating an inclusive environment for people from different backgrounds right from senior management right down to store levels (LGBQ)
reviews.cons: The tills are hectic, as your security, refund person, customer service and managing the tills all in one, But for me being put under pressure allowed me to become a better manager as I learnt to stay calm under pressure Not enough hours but its retail so can’t complain , that was the only reason I left, was for full time work Shift work, I didn’t mind it as it gave variety from running loan in the morning to closing store at night They are bringing in self service check outs, not a fan of theses as I believe Aldi may cut staff levels
reviews.summary: Aldi will make you a great Leader
reviews.advice: Rotate jobs within the store Make the special tables able to link up so you can move a lot of tables at once Give a training module for the Aldi phone plans as when customers ask its looks bad when none of us in store can answer any of their questions and we have no pamphlets to show them

reviews.pros: - pay is good - flexible working hours.
reviews.cons: - sometimes very boring especially when you are in Till. - morning shifts are very tiring
reviews.summary: Good place to start a part time job

reviews.pros: Good pay Good amount of breaks Nice variety of tasks
reviews.cons: Mistakes are the main focus rather than good behaviour Everything is timed, have to be fast-er A lot of work, you’ll be sweating My store was always running behind leading to staying back after close Lazy managers
reviews.advice: Management should recognise and reward good behaviour to set positive morale in the store. Managers shouldn’t be in the office for hours at a time, help on the floor is crucial and always needed. Stop complaining when we call for a manager. It’s your job. As a manager. To aid and assist when we bell for manager.
